1
00:00:23,190 --> 00:00:25,950
POLITICAL CONSTITUTION

2
00:00:26,070 --> 00:00:28,150
OF THE UNITED STATES OF MEXICO

3
00:02:45,670 --> 00:02:50,150
HEROD'S LAW

4
00:02:51,190 --> 00:02:55,070
My God, they lynched a Mayor
just when the President...

5
00:02:55,190 --> 00:02:58,430
is talking about modernity
and social peace.

6
00:02:58,510 --> 00:03:00,070
Don't fuck this up, López.

7
00:03:00,190 --> 00:03:05,910
Don't worry, Mr. Governor. We've taken
the necessary steps to deal with it.

8
00:03:06,030 --> 00:03:09,390
I'm talking about
the Presidency of Mexico, no less.

9
00:03:09,510 --> 00:03:13,230
If I'm not careful, that asshole
Ruiz Cortinez will beat me to it.

10
00:03:13,470 --> 00:03:15,310
I want to get through this clean.

11
00:03:15,390 --> 00:03:20,110
If I don't get at least a ministry,
I'm out of the game.

12
00:03:20,670 --> 00:03:23,110
Don't worry, General.

13
00:03:23,230 --> 00:03:28,070
I assure you that
you are valuable to the party.

14
00:03:28,150 --> 00:03:31,270
Look, López.

15
00:03:31,390 --> 00:03:34,430
If you want to be governor,
everything must be resolved.

16
00:03:34,510 --> 00:03:37,070
If people mention our state,
they must speak well of it.

17
00:03:38,150 --> 00:03:40,950
You know better than anyone
who elects who around here.

18
00:03:41,070 --> 00:03:45,510
If you want my job, don't give me any
problems like this San Pedro business.

19
00:03:45,630 --> 00:03:51,790
Lynching a mayor when President Alemán
speaks of modernity and justice.

20
00:03:51,910 --> 00:03:53,430
Don't fuck this up, Ramírez.

21
00:03:54,350 --> 00:03:57,790
Don't worry, Licenciado.
We'll find someone soon.

22
00:03:57,870 --> 00:04:00,510
This has to be resolved today.

23
00:04:00,630 --> 00:04:03,550
I need to arrange things
with the governor.

24
00:04:03,670 --> 00:04:08,470
He said I've been chosen,
so get looking.

25
00:04:08,550 --> 00:04:10,350
Find me someone not too bright.

26
00:04:10,470 --> 00:04:12,750
He will hold the post
for three or four months.

27
00:04:12,870 --> 00:04:13,990
What do you think of him?

28
00:04:16,710 --> 00:04:20,350
- Who's he?
- The least bad, but he's straight.

29
00:04:20,430 --> 00:04:23,150
- He threatened to quit the party.
- No, no.

30
00:04:24,030 --> 00:04:24,710
And this?

31
00:04:24,830 --> 00:04:26,990
That's ''Sticky Fingers''.

32
00:04:27,070 --> 00:04:30,550
I doubt he'd accept a shitty job
like Mayor of San Pedro.

33
00:04:32,590 --> 00:04:34,870
And this one who looks
like Tintán. Vargas?

34
00:04:34,950 --> 00:04:38,030
He's been in the party for
years. He joined when I did.

35
00:04:38,150 --> 00:04:40,110
He's a good man. He'll
probably accept.

36
00:04:40,190 --> 00:04:41,990
What do you mean
''a good man''?

37
00:04:42,110 --> 00:04:43,150
I mean he's stupid.

38
00:04:45,430 --> 00:04:47,750
Fine. Go and get him.

39
00:04:47,870 --> 00:04:50,350
''Institutional Revolutionary Party
-Juan Vargas''

40
00:05:18,350 --> 00:05:21,270
''Cleaning Department
Supervisor''

41
00:05:30,430 --> 00:05:31,750
Good morning.

42
00:05:33,830 --> 00:05:35,430
Ramírez?

43
00:05:36,590 --> 00:05:37,470
Ramírez!

44
00:05:38,270 --> 00:05:42,150
Fucking Vargas, you have to
call me Licenciado now. Okay?

45
00:05:42,270 --> 00:05:44,590
It's been a long time.
Is that car yours?

46
00:05:44,710 --> 00:05:49,150
Yes. Licenciado López sent me.
He wants a word with you.

47
00:05:49,270 --> 00:05:54,230
The governor's secretary?
What about?

48
00:05:54,350 --> 00:05:58,310
You're in a fine mess. Hurry up.
He's waiting for us.

49
00:06:08,230 --> 00:06:09,190
Go in.

50
00:06:10,990 --> 00:06:12,270
Wait for me here.

51
00:06:12,910 --> 00:06:14,550
And behave, asshole.

52
00:06:47,470 --> 00:06:49,870
Yes, tell him I'll call him.

53
00:06:53,030 --> 00:06:54,510
Afternoon, Vargas.

54
00:06:54,630 --> 00:06:56,510
-It's an honor, Licenciado.
-Sit down.

55
00:06:58,110 --> 00:07:01,150
I'll be straight with you, Vargas.

56
00:07:01,270 --> 00:07:05,710
As you know, modernity
has at last come to our country.

57
00:07:05,790 --> 00:07:08,710
We must embody the ideals
of the revolution...

58
00:07:08,790 --> 00:07:12,670
make President Alemán's
words reality...

59
00:07:12,790 --> 00:07:14,550
help the country advance...

60
00:07:14,630 --> 00:07:19,310
stamp out corruption, especially the mess
caused by those who don't agree.

61
00:07:20,350 --> 00:07:24,830
Certain government
workers don't understand this.

62
00:07:24,910 --> 00:07:27,670
They have taken advantage of their posts
to engage in private business..

63
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:29,750
and grow rich at the
nation's cost.

64
00:07:29,870 --> 00:07:34,270
This country needs true patriots,
people like you.

65
00:07:34,950 --> 00:07:36,190
Thanks, Licenciado.

66
00:07:38,230 --> 00:07:39,710
I'm going to need your help.

67
00:07:41,230 --> 00:07:44,030
Just tell me who
I have to kill.

68
00:07:45,510 --> 00:07:48,070
No, no, Vargas. Times have changed.

69
00:07:49,350 --> 00:07:51,550
You heard what happened
in San Pedro de los Saguaros?

70
00:07:52,670 --> 00:07:56,230
The people rioted.
There was some kind of problem there...

71
00:07:56,310 --> 00:07:58,070
and now there is nobody in charge.

72
00:07:58,190 --> 00:08:04,510
We have to appoint a temporary mayor
who will keep order until the elections.

73
00:08:05,950 --> 00:08:07,110
Right.

74
00:08:10,310 --> 00:08:13,190
And how can I help, Licenciado?

75
00:08:14,510 --> 00:08:17,870
You came up short, Ramírez.
Don't be a fool, Vargas.

76
00:08:17,990 --> 00:08:22,150
The party has taken note of
you and I'm informing you...

77
00:08:22,230 --> 00:08:27,710
that you are to be temporary Mayor
of San Pedro de los Saguaros.

78
00:08:27,830 --> 00:08:29,830
M-Mayor? Me?

79
00:08:29,950 --> 00:08:33,310
So you see how the revolution
is just with people like you.

80
00:08:33,430 --> 00:08:37,430
I trust you totally, Vargas.

81
00:08:37,510 --> 00:08:39,230
Totally.

82
00:08:39,350 --> 00:08:44,550
This is a real opportunity. Maybe even
the start of a great political career.

83
00:08:44,670 --> 00:08:45,630
That's right, isn't it?

84
00:08:45,750 --> 00:08:51,710
Go to San Pedro and fulfill President
Alemán and Governor Sanchez's promises:

85
00:08:51,830 --> 00:08:54,390
''Modernity and social justice.''

86
00:08:54,510 --> 00:08:57,990
But listen
I don't want any problems.

87
00:08:58,070 --> 00:09:01,470
If they mention San Pedro de los
Saguaros in the capital...

88
00:09:01,550 --> 00:09:04,070
they'd better say nice things.

89
00:09:04,190 --> 00:09:06,110
No messing things up.
Understood?

90
00:09:06,190 --> 00:09:10,110
Don't worry, Licenciado.
How can I thank you?

91
00:09:10,190 --> 00:09:12,150
Thank the party.

92
00:09:12,230 --> 00:09:15,910
Remember:
''We owe everything to the party''.

93
00:09:17,190 --> 00:09:18,630
There's more.

94
00:09:18,750 --> 00:09:20,350
Here, take this.

95
00:09:20,470 --> 00:09:24,190
Governor Sanchez himself
gave it to me...

96
00:09:25,110 --> 00:09:29,310
so it's sure to bring you luck.
There.

97
00:09:30,230 --> 00:09:32,110
Thank you, Licenciado.

98
00:09:32,230 --> 00:09:35,110
Now all you have
to do is go to work.

99
00:09:35,230 --> 00:09:36,190
Yes, sir.

100
00:09:37,230 --> 00:09:41,110
Ramírez, brother,
thank you, thank you.

101
00:09:41,230 --> 00:09:42,110
Licenciado!

102
00:09:42,230 --> 00:09:45,190
Thank you, Licenciado.
Excuse me, Licenciado.

103
00:09:57,230 --> 00:10:03,350
Here you go, Ramírez.
President Alemán gave me this as a gift.

104
00:10:03,470 --> 00:10:06,230
Now it's yours
for finding me that fool.

105
00:10:19,110 --> 00:10:23,830
Nothing more and nothing less
than mayor, honey.

106
00:10:25,270 --> 00:10:29,270
Finally, after so many years
in that party...

107
00:10:29,390 --> 00:10:32,190
something good happens to us.

108
00:10:32,270 --> 00:10:34,390
Are you happy, sweetheart?

109
00:10:37,270 --> 00:10:40,190
And this is just the start.
You'll see.

110
00:10:40,270 --> 00:10:43,590
If I do well,
next stop is State Deputy...

111
00:10:43,710 --> 00:10:46,670
then Congressman, my golden dream.

112
00:10:48,310 --> 00:10:52,270
Just imagine, your name
on a plaque in the National Congress.

113
00:10:53,310 --> 00:10:56,910
Better still, imagine:

114
00:10:56,990 --> 00:10:59,430
Senator and Mrs. Vargas.

115
00:10:59,550 --> 00:11:01,150
That doesn't sound bad.

116
00:11:01,230 --> 00:11:06,110
Not bad at all, Mrs. Senator.
Not bad at all.

117
00:11:16,270 --> 00:11:20,950
Excuse me. How far is it to
San Pedro de los Saguaros?

118
00:12:01,230 --> 00:12:03,190
Good afternoon.

119
00:12:05,230 --> 00:12:07,190
Excuse me.
Do you speak Spanish?

120
00:12:08,430 --> 00:12:10,190
I think we're lost.

121
00:12:10,310 --> 00:12:13,190
How far is it to
San Pedro de los Saguaros?

122
00:12:13,270 --> 00:12:18,790
It's right here.
You must be the new mayor.

123
00:12:20,830 --> 00:12:22,830
I've been waiting for you
since yesterday.

124
00:12:23,910 --> 00:12:27,470
I'm Carlos Pek, your secretary.

125
00:12:28,710 --> 00:12:30,790
Juan Vargas, at your service.

126
00:12:30,910 --> 00:12:34,550
President Alemán and
Governor Sanchez...

127
00:12:34,670 --> 00:12:38,550
have sent me to bring
modernity and social justice.

128
00:12:40,670 --> 00:12:42,150
We've arrived.

129
00:12:47,270 --> 00:12:49,230
Welcome, Madam.

130
00:12:52,270 --> 00:12:53,270
Here?

131
00:12:59,110 --> 00:13:03,310
''TOWN HALL''

132
00:13:11,230 --> 00:13:14,910
You should go
and see your office,Juan.

133
00:13:14,990 --> 00:13:18,590
What for? This is enough for me.

134
00:13:18,710 --> 00:13:21,110
A fucking little backwater.

135
00:13:21,230 --> 00:13:23,150
We're better off
in the garbage dump.

136
00:13:23,230 --> 00:13:26,230
Don't say that.
You were nobody at the dump.

137
00:13:26,310 --> 00:13:28,230
Here you are the chief.

138
00:13:30,270 --> 00:13:32,910
The mayor.

139
00:13:34,190 --> 00:13:37,870
Didn't you hear how they even
called you Licenciado?

140
00:13:37,990 --> 00:13:41,230
- He did call me Licenciado, didn't he?
- Yes.

141
00:13:43,270 --> 00:13:44,790
Do you honestly think
we are better off here?

142
00:13:45,590 --> 00:13:48,990
Of course. Don't you see?

143
00:13:49,070 --> 00:13:51,550
Here we're important people.

144
00:13:52,350 --> 00:13:57,230
It's just the start,
but we have to be very, very...

145
00:13:58,670 --> 00:13:59,270
smart.

146
00:14:02,310 --> 00:14:03,670
Good morning.

147
00:14:10,350 --> 00:14:11,790
Pek? Pek?

148
00:14:13,550 --> 00:14:18,190
Word is out that there's a new mayor.
Everyone wants their affairs dealt with.

149
00:14:19,630 --> 00:14:22,030
Please tell them I'll
see them later.

150
00:14:46,270 --> 00:14:49,230
Alright, let's get to work.

151
00:14:53,510 --> 00:14:56,830
- What's this, Pek?
- Unresolved matters, Licenciado.

152
00:14:56,950 --> 00:15:01,070
There are many more, but these
are the most urgent.

153
00:15:02,030 --> 00:15:05,110
These are agrarian problems.
This is--

154
00:15:05,230 --> 00:15:06,830
Do you know what, Pek?

155
00:15:06,950 --> 00:15:11,910
I think we should talk a stroll
so that I can get to know the place.

156
00:15:11,990 --> 00:15:13,350
Don't you think so?

157
00:15:13,470 --> 00:15:19,870
The village is very small--
less than 1 00 inhabitants.

158
00:15:19,990 --> 00:15:26,550
Most of us Indians
who've lived here all our lives.

159
00:15:26,670 --> 00:15:28,110
Good morning.

160
00:15:30,230 --> 00:15:32,630
Don't be offended, Licenciado.

161
00:15:32,750 --> 00:15:35,030
They are good people...

162
00:15:35,150 --> 00:15:39,750
but most of them
don't even speak Spanish.

163
00:15:39,870 --> 00:15:41,270
Really?

164
00:15:41,390 --> 00:15:43,150
Don't they learn it at school?

165
00:15:43,270 --> 00:15:45,310
Licenciado.

166
00:15:46,230 --> 00:15:48,230
Look.

167
00:15:49,390 --> 00:15:53,030
- That was the school.
- What happened?

168
00:15:53,150 --> 00:15:56,510
They built it in the days
ofTata Cardenas.

169
00:15:56,590 --> 00:16:01,310
When the government changed,
they stopped paying the teacher...

170
00:16:01,390 --> 00:16:02,830
and one day he left.

171
00:16:03,990 --> 00:16:06,150
The same old story Licenciado.

172
00:16:06,230 --> 00:16:09,790
What about the doors,
windows and everything?

173
00:16:09,870 --> 00:16:12,190
That was one of
your colleagues.

174
00:16:12,270 --> 00:16:13,310
What did he do?

175
00:16:13,430 --> 00:16:16,510
One day, the bastard sold them...

176
00:16:16,630 --> 00:16:18,870
along with the blackboard
benches and anything of value.

177
00:16:18,990 --> 00:16:20,150
I don't believe it.

178
00:16:20,270 --> 00:16:23,390
He didn't sell the walls because
nobody wanted to buy them.

179
00:16:23,510 --> 00:16:28,230
He'd have sold the whole
village given the chance.

180
00:16:30,230 --> 00:16:36,110
This has happened
with every mayor we've had Licenciado.

181
00:16:37,510 --> 00:16:40,190
Listen Pek. What happened to
my predecessor?

182
00:16:40,270 --> 00:16:42,390
Why did he quit?

183
00:16:43,790 --> 00:16:45,670
Licenciado...

184
00:16:47,070 --> 00:16:47,830
Didn't they tell you?

185
00:16:48,830 --> 00:16:51,270
They cut off his head
with a machete!

186
00:16:51,390 --> 00:16:52,670
What?

187
00:16:54,310 --> 00:16:58,710
They cut it off, and that's not the end
of the story of the Mayors of San Pedro.

188
00:16:58,790 --> 00:17:02,870
Another one was hanged,
another almost burned alive.

189
00:17:02,950 --> 00:17:05,550
Three mayors killed in 5 years.

190
00:17:06,910 --> 00:17:09,150
Why would they send me?

191
00:17:09,230 --> 00:17:11,230
I don't know...

192
00:17:11,350 --> 00:17:14,390
but they must have done
something, no?

193
00:17:15,710 --> 00:17:19,030
Who knows?
But...just in case.

194
00:17:28,470 --> 00:17:29,670
Good morning.

195
00:17:34,270 --> 00:17:35,350
What's this, Pek?

196
00:17:35,470 --> 00:17:37,110
Manslaughter.

197
00:17:42,270 --> 00:17:45,910
Licenciado Vargas,
This is Doctor Morales.

198
00:17:47,030 --> 00:17:48,110
Pleased to meet you, Doctor.

199
00:17:48,230 --> 00:17:52,150
Six bullets.
This, like all the evils in San Pedro...

200
00:17:52,270 --> 00:17:56,310
is due to that brothel.
I suppose you know it.

201
00:17:56,430 --> 00:17:57,510
No, no.

202
00:17:57,630 --> 00:17:59,470
With him, that's eight dead men...

203
00:17:59,590 --> 00:18:03,590
not counting the diseases
half the village is infected with.

204
00:18:03,710 --> 00:18:06,110
Something must be done
about that place!

205
00:18:06,190 --> 00:18:10,870
Don't worry, Doctor. I'll take
the necessary steps to close...

206
00:18:10,990 --> 00:18:12,390
It's your duty!

207
00:18:12,510 --> 00:18:15,190
I've only arrived. I promise...

208
00:18:15,310 --> 00:18:20,870
It's very easy. Do your job
and everything will be fine.

209
00:18:20,990 --> 00:18:24,830
If not I promise you'll regret
ever coming to San Pedro.

210
00:18:32,830 --> 00:18:34,910
Who's this man, Pek?

211
00:18:35,030 --> 00:18:40,110
Doctor Morales is someone to
watch out for, Licenciado.

212
00:18:41,150 --> 00:18:44,550
He's been the PAN candidate
for mayor four times...

213
00:18:44,670 --> 00:18:46,550
and always complains about fraud.

214
00:18:47,710 --> 00:18:49,070
Can you believe it?

215
00:18:49,190 --> 00:18:54,110
From now on,
he's going to be your worst nightmare.

216
00:18:54,230 --> 00:18:56,630
So it seems.

217
00:18:56,710 --> 00:18:58,910
You can't imagine it.

218
00:19:01,670 --> 00:19:04,990
- What shall we do, Pek?
- He had no relatives.

219
00:19:05,110 --> 00:19:06,790
I suppose it's up to us.

220
00:19:43,950 --> 00:19:45,310
We don't open until eight.

221
00:19:54,670 --> 00:19:57,350
-I want to speak with your boss.
-She's sleeping.

222
00:19:57,430 --> 00:20:00,190
Tell her it's the new mayor.

223
00:20:01,430 --> 00:20:03,150
Wait here.

224
00:20:11,750 --> 00:20:13,630
She says come in.

225
00:20:29,150 --> 00:20:32,630
Miss, ah, how much
are you charging?

226
00:20:39,470 --> 00:20:41,150
What can I do for you?

227
00:20:42,190 --> 00:20:47,390
Good morning. Sorry to wake
you up at this hour, Doña...

228
00:20:47,510 --> 00:20:49,670
-Lupe.
-Juan Vargas, at your service.

229
00:20:49,750 --> 00:20:52,510
Sit down, Licenciado.
Get lost, you.

230
00:20:55,990 --> 00:20:58,990
- A drink?
- Not in working hours.

231
00:20:59,110 --> 00:21:02,950
Well, a little shot never
did any harm.

232
00:21:04,270 --> 00:21:06,990
So you're the new mayor.

233
00:21:07,110 --> 00:21:09,470
At your service, Madam.

234
00:21:09,590 --> 00:21:11,190
And the thing is...

235
00:21:13,950 --> 00:21:15,190
How can I say?

236
00:21:15,270 --> 00:21:20,550
...that certain people are not
happy about your business.

237
00:21:21,710 --> 00:21:26,550
Ah, Licenciado, you're just
like all the others...

238
00:21:27,950 --> 00:21:31,030
...coming here for your
bribe, right?

239
00:21:35,910 --> 00:21:39,550
No, madam, nothing of the kind.
It's just that people--

240
00:21:39,630 --> 00:21:44,870
People or Dr. Morales? That old
son of a bitch won't leave me alone.

241
00:21:44,990 --> 00:21:48,150
He turns the Indians
and everyone against me.

242
00:21:48,270 --> 00:21:49,590
It's not just the Doctor.

243
00:21:49,670 --> 00:21:53,870
There's a corpse outside--
someone who was shot here yesterday.

244
00:21:53,990 --> 00:21:58,550
A corpse? No, Licenciado.
Someone's pulling your leg.

245
00:21:58,670 --> 00:22:01,590
- Nothing like happened here.
- The thing is...

246
00:22:01,710 --> 00:22:05,350
No, Licenciado, everything is in order.

247
00:22:05,470 --> 00:22:10,270
Don Alfredo Garcia who was mayor
before you, gave me all the permits.

248
00:22:10,390 --> 00:22:12,910
Are you going to take
this or not?

249
00:22:14,390 --> 00:22:17,750
